{"title_page": "Frances Mercer", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name          = Frances Mercer\n| image         = \n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = \n| birth_date    = {{Birth date|1915|10|21}}\n| birth_place   = [[New Rochelle, New York]]\n| death_date    = {{Death date and age|2000|11|12|1915|10|21}}\n| death_place   = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]\n| occupation    = Actress\n| years_active  =\n}}\n\n'''Frances Mercer''' (October 21, 1915 \u2013 November 12, 2000) was an American actress. She appeared in the films ''[[Vivacious Lady]]'', ''[[Blind Alibi]]'', ''[[Crime Ring (film)|Crime Ring]]'', ''[[Smashing the Rackets]]'', ''[[The Mad Miss Manton]]'', ''[[Annabel Takes a Tour]]'', ''[[Beauty for the Asking]]'', ''[[Society Lawyer]]'', ''[[The Story of Vernon and Irene Castle]]'', ''[[Piccadilly Incident]]'', ''[[There's Always Tomorrow (1956 film)|There's Always Tomorrow]]'' and ''[[Young and Dangerous (1957 film)|Young and Dangerous]]''.\n\nShe died on November 12, 2000, in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]] at age 85.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2000/nov/08/local/me-48846 |title=Frances Mercer; Movie Actress, Early TV Star |publisher=Articles.latimes.com |date=2000-11-08 |accessdate=2018-09-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2000/11/22/arts/frances-mercer-85-model-turned-actress.html |title=Frances Mercer, 85, Model-Turned-Actress |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=2000-11-22 |accessdate=2018-09-25}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n|1938|| ''[[Vivacious Lady]]'' || Helen ||\n|-\n|1938|| ''[[Blind Alibi]]'' || Ellen ||\n|-\n|1938|| ''[[Crime Ring (film)|Crime Ring]]'' || Judy Allen ||\n|-\n|1938|| ''[[Smashing the Rackets]]'' || Susan 'Pat' Lane ||\n|-\n|1938|| ''[[The Mad Miss Manton]]'' || Helen Frayne ||\n|-\n|1938|| ''[[Annabel Takes a Tour]]'' || Natalie Preston ||\n|-\n|1939|| ''[[Beauty for the Asking]]'' || Patricia Wharton ||\n|-\n|193