{"title_page": "Frances Denny Drake", "text_new": "{{Underlinked|date=April 2020}}\n\n'''Frances Denny Drake''' (1797\u20131872), was an American actress, foremost known as a tragedienne.<ref>Robin O. Warren, ''[https://books.google.se/books?id=gwBODQAAQBAJ&pg=PA20&lpg=PA20&dq=french+theatre+charleston+alexandre+placide&source=bl&ots=lS55fHm7Tg&sig=ACfU3U1yWedlFsftjIlEjmhjVTm2i0I3lA&hl=sv&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjX0_bntKDiAhU7xcQBHWtaCzgQ6AEwCXoECAcQAQ#v=onepage&q=french%20theatre%20charleston%20alexandre%20placide&f=false Women on Southern Stages, 1800\u20131865: Performance, Gender and Identity]''</ref> She had a successful career from 1815 onward, toured all the United States and has been described as the perhaps most well-known actress in America prior to [[Charlotte Cushman]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Expand Swedish|Frances Denny Drake|date=June 2019}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:19th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:American stage actresses]]\n[[Category:1797 births]]\n[[Category:1875 deaths]]\n", "text_old": "'''Frances Denny Drake''' (1797\u20131872), was an American actress, foremost known as a tragedienne. <ref>Robin O. Warren, ''[https://books.google.se/books?id=gwBODQAAQBAJ&pg=PA20&lpg=PA20&dq=french+theatre+charleston+alexandre+placide&source=bl&ots=lS55fHm7Tg&sig=ACfU3U1yWedlFsftjIlEjmhjVTm2i0I3lA&hl=sv&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjX0_bntKDiAhU7xcQBHWtaCzgQ6AEwCXoECAcQAQ#v=onepage&q=french%20theatre%20charleston%20alexandre%20placide&f=false Women on Southern Stages, 1800\u20131865: Performance, Gender and Identity]''</ref> She had a successful career from 1815 onward, toured all the United States and has been described as the perhaps most well-known actress in America prior to [[Charlotte Cushman]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Expand Swedish|Frances Denny Drake|date=June 2019}}\n\n\n[[Category:19th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:American stage actresses]]\n[[Category:1797 births]]\n[[Category:1875 deaths]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control, addedunderlinkedtag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frances_Denny_Drake"}
{"title_page": "Resort", "text_new": "{{short description|Self-contained commercial establishment which attempts to provide for most of a vacationer's wants}}\n{{Other uses}}\n{{More citations needed|date=December 2007}}\n[[File:Town and Country fh000023.jpg|thumb|right|Resorts combine a hotel and a variety of recreations, such as [[swimming pool]]s, as shown here in San Diego, California]]\n[[File:pyramid resort jasper.JPG|thumb|right|[[Kayak]]ing provided by a lakeside resort in [[Jasper, Alberta]]]]\n\nA '''resort''' ([[North American English]]) is a self-contained commercial establishment that tries to be a good decision but the first time I went to the book and it was a good decision I did not get a good book it also provide most of a [[vacation]]er's wants, such as food, drink, [[lodging]], [[sport]]s, [[entertainment]], and [[shopping]], on the premises. The term ''resort'' may be used for a [[hotel]] property that provides an array of amenities, typically including entertainment and recreational activities. A hotel is frequently a central feature of a resort, such as the [[Grand Hotel (Mackinac Island)|Grand Hotel]] at [[Mackinac Island, Michigan]]. Some resorts are also condominium complexes that are timeshares or owed fractionally or wholly owned condominium. A resort is not always a commercial establishment operated by a single company, but in the late 20th century, that sort of facility became more common.\n\nIn [[British English]], \"resort\" means a town which people visit for holidays and days out which usually contains hotels at which such holidaymakers stay.  Examples would include [[Blackpool]] and [[Brighton]].\n\n== Destination resort ==\n[[File:Banff Springs Hotel1.jpg|thumb|left|[[Banff Springs Hotel]], [[Banff, Alberta|Banff]], [[Alberta]], Canada]]\nA [[destination hotel|destination resort]] is a resort that itself contains the necessary guest attraction capabilities so it does not need to be near a destination (town, historic site, theme park, or other) to attract its patrons. A commercial establishment at a resort destination such as a recreational area, a scenic or historic site, [[amusement park]], a gaming facility, or other tourist attraction may compete with other businesses at a destination. Consequently, another quality of a destination resort is that it offers food, drink, lodging, sports, entertainment, and shopping within the facility so that guests have no need to leave the facility throughout their stay.  Commonly, the facilities are of higher quality than would be expected if one were to stay at a hotel or eat in a town's restaurants. Some examples are Atlantis in the [[Bahamas]]; the [[Walt Disney World Resort]], near [[Orlando, Florida]], [[United States]]; [[PortAventura World]], near [[Barcelona]] on the [[Costa Daurada]] in [[Spain]]; Costa do Sau\u00edpe, [[Northeastern Brazil]]; Laguna Phuket, [[Thailand]] and Sun City, near [[Johannesburg]], [[South Africa]]. Closely related to resorts are convention and large meeting sites. Generally, they occur in cities, where special meeting halls, together with ample accommodations and varied dining and entertainment, are provided.\n\n== All-inclusive resort ==\n[[File:Happy Life Entrance.JPG|thumb|Entrance of an all-inclusive resort in [[Egypt]]]]\nAn all-inclusive resort charges a fixed price that includes most or all items.  At a minimum, most inclusive resorts include lodging, unlimited food, drink, sports activities, and entertainment for the fixed price. In recent years, the number of resorts in the United States offering \"all-inclusive\" amenities has decreased dramatically. In 1961, over half offered such plans, but in 2007, less than a tenth do so.<ref>{{cite news |first= |last= |authorlink= |coauthors= |title= American Plan resorts among last of vanishing breed |url= http://www.cnn.com/2007/TRAVEL/06/28/american.plan.ap/index.html|work=[[Associated Press]] |publisher=CNN.com |date=June 28, 2007 |accessdate= 2007-06-29 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20071012183847/http://cnn.com/2007/TRAVEL/06/28/american.plan.ap/index.html <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-10-12}}</ref>\n\nAll-inclusive resorts are found in the [[Caribbean]], particularly in [[Dominican Republic]]; in [[Egypt]], and elsewhere. Notable examples are [[Club Med]], [[Sandals Resorts]], and [[Beaches Resorts]].\n\nAn all-inclusive resort includes three meals daily, [[soft drink]]s, most [[alcoholic drink]]s, [[gratuities]], and usually other services in the price. Many also offer sports and other activities included in the price as well. They are often located in warmer regions. The all-inclusive model originated in the [[Club Med]] resorts, which were founded by the Belgian [[G\u00e9rard Blitz (entrepreneur)|G\u00e9rard Blitz]].<ref name=\"Garrett Nagle 1999\">{{cite book|title=Tourism, Leisure and Recreation|author=Garrett Nagle|year= 1999|publisher=Nelson Thornes|isbn=0-17-444705-1}}</ref>\n\nSome all-inclusive resorts are designed for specific groups. For example, some resorts cater for adults only, and even more-specialized properties accept couples only. Other all-inclusive resorts are geared toward families, with facilities like craft centers, game rooms, and water parks to keep children of all ages entertained. All-inclusive resorts are also very popular locations for destination weddings.\n[[File:Boating Resort in Vijayawada.jpg|250px|thumb|Boating resort in Vijayawada, India]]\n\n== Recreation ==\nA [[destination spa|spa resort]] is a short l-term residential/lodging facility with the primary purpose of providing individual services for spa goers to develop healthy habits. Historically, many such spas were developed at the location of natural hot springs or sources of mineral waters. Typically over a seven-day stay, such facilities provide a comprehensive program that includes spa services, physical fitness activities, healthy diet programs, and special interest programming.\n\nGolf resorts are resorts that cater specifically to the sport of [[golf]], and they include access to one or more golf courses and/or clubhouses. Golf resorts typically provide golf packages that provide visitors with all greens and cart fees, range balls, accommodations, and meals.\n\n[[File:Male Ciche.jpg|thumb|right|220px|A view of a typical ski resort and ski lifts]]\nIn [[North America]], a ski resort is generally a destination resort in a ski area. The term is less likely to refer to a town or village.\n\n[[File:Las Vegas 63.jpg|thumb|The [[Las Vegas strip]] in 2009]]\nA megaresort is a type of destination resort of an exceptionally-large size, such as those along the [[Las Vegas Strip]]. In [[Singapore]], ''[[integrated resort]]'' is a [[euphemism]] for a [[casino]]-based destination resort.\n\nA [[holiday village]] is a type of self-contained resort in [[Europe]] whose accommodation is generally in [[villa]]s.  A [[holiday camp]], in the [[United Kingdom]], refers to a resort whose accommodation is in [[chalet]]s or [[static caravan]]s.\n\n== Timeshare ==\nThere are more than 1500 [[timeshare]] resorts in the United States that are operated by major hospitality, timeshare-specific, or independent companies. They represent 198,000 residences and nearly 9 million owners, who pay an average $880 per year in maintenance fees. A reported 16% of the residences became [[vacation rentals]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nxtbook.com/ygsreprints/ARDA/g51820_arda_july2015/#/28|title=2015 State of the Industry |publisher=Developments|accessdate=July 1, 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Notable historic resorts ==\n* [[Baiae]], Italy, a famous historic resort of the ancient world that was popular over 2000 years ago. \n* [[Capri]], an island near [[Naples]], Italy, has attracted visitors since Roman times.\n* [[Monte Ne]], near [[Rogers, Arkansas]], a famous historic resort which was active in the early 20th century. At its peak, more than 10,000 people a year visited its hotels. Two of its hotels, Missouri Row and Oklahoma Row, were the largest log buildings in the world. Monte Ne closed in the 1930s and was ultimately submerged under [[Beaver Lake (Arkansas)|Beaver Lake]] in the 1960s.\n* Tawawa House, also known as Tawawa Springs or Xenia Springs, inspired [[Dolen Perkins-Valdez]] to write her [[debut novel]], ''Wench'' (2010),<ref>{{cite book|title=Wench|author=Perkins-Vadez, Dolen|publisher=Amistad|date=2010|asin=B004NE8RZ4}}</ref> when she read about it in an autobiography of [[W.E.B. Dubois]]. The book mentioned in passing that the land for [[Wilberforce University]] had once been used for a privately owned resort called Tawawa House, where white slave owners would bring the black slaves that they kept as mistresses.<ref>{{cite news|last1=O'Neal Parker|first1=Lonnae|title=A tender spot in master-slave relations|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2011/01/21/AR2011012102960.html|accessdate=15 April 2015|work=Washington Post}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hmdb.org/marker.asp?marker=14058|website=The Historical Marker Database|title= Old Wilberforce University Campus at Tawawa Springs |accessdate=May 28, 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Resort towns ==\nTowns that are resorts or in which [[tourism]] or vacationing is a major part of the local activity are sometimes called [[resort towns]]. If by the sea, they are called [[seaside resort]]s.  Inland resorts include [[ski resort]]s, [[mountain resort]]s and [[spa town]]s. Well-known resort towns include [[Punta Cana]] in [[Dominican Republic]], [[Bandipur]] in [[Nepal]], [[Bali]] in Indonesia, [[Sochi]] in [[Russia]], Mount Lebanon Tourism in [[Lebanon]], [[Barizo]] in [[Spain]], [[Cortina d'Ampezzo]] in Italy, [[Druskininkai]] in [[Lithuania]], [[Canc\u00fan]] in Mexico, [[Newport, Rhode Island]], and [[Key West, Florida]], in the United States, [[Ischgl]] in [[Austria]], [[St. Moritz]] in [[Switzerland]], [[Blackpool]] in the [[United Kingdom]] and [[Malam Jabba]] in [[Pakistan]].\n\n[[File:HuvafenFushi.jpg|thumb|A [[resort island]] in the [[Maldives]]]]\nA [[resort island]] is an island or an archipelago that contains resorts, hotels, restaurants, tourist attractions, and its amenities. [[Maldives]] is considered to have the best island resorts, which have become famous among the top celebrities and sportspersons around the world.\n\n[[File:Miamimetroarea.jpg|right|thumb|[[Miami Beach, Florida|Miami Beach]] in Florida]]\n[[Seaside resort]]s are located on a coast. In the United Kingdom, many seaside towns have turned to other entertainment industries, and some of them have much nightlife. The cinemas and theatres often remain to become host to a number of pubs, bars, restaurants, and nightclubs. Most of their entertainment facilities cater to local people, and the beaches still remain popular during the summer months.\n\nIn Europe and North America, [[ski resort]]s are towns and villages in ski areas, with support services for skiing such as hotels and [[chalet]]s, equipment rental, [[ski school]]s and [[ski lift]]s to access the slopes.\n\nResorts for different purposes also exist. An example is [[Yulara]], [[Northern Territory]], which exists to serve [[Uluru|Uluru (Ayers Rock)]] and [[Kata Tjuta|Kata Tjuta (The Olgas)]] in [[Australia]].\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Boutique hotel]]\n*[[Condo hotel]]\n*[[Destination club]]\n*[[Resort architecture]]\n*[[Sanatorium (resort)]]\n*[[Seaside resort]]\n*[[Spa]]\n*[[Vacation rental]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Commons category|Resorts}}\n{{Wiktionary}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{tourism}}\n\n[[Category:Resorts| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Self-contained commercial establishment which attempts to provide for most of a vacationer's wants}}\n{{Other uses}}\n{{More citations needed|date=December 2007}}\n[[File:Town and Country fh000023.jpg|thumb|right|Resorts combine a hotel and a variety of recreations, such as [[swimming pool]]s, as shown here in San Diego, California]]\n[[File:pyramid resort jasper.JPG|thumb|right|[[Kayak]]ing provided by a lakeside resort in [[Jasper, Alberta]]]]\n\nA '''resort''' ([[North American English]]) is a self-contained commercial establishment that tries to provide most of a [[vacation]]er's wants, such as food, drink, [[lodging]], [[sport]]s, [[entertainment]], and [[shopping]], on the premises. The term ''resort'' may be used for a [[hotel]] property that provides an array of amenities, typically including entertainment and recreational activities. A hotel is frequently a central feature of a resort, such as the [[Grand Hotel (Mackinac Island)|Grand Hotel]] at [[Mackinac Island, Michigan]]. Some resorts are also condominium complexes that are timeshares or owed fractionally or wholly owned condominium. A resort is not always a commercial establishment operated by a single company, but in the late 20th century, that sort of facility became more common.\n\nIn [[British English]], \"resort\" means a town which people visit for holidays and days out which usually contains hotels at which such holidaymakers stay.  Examples would include [[Blackpool]] and [[Brighton]].\n\n== Destination resort ==\n[[File:Banff Springs Hotel1.jpg|thumb|left|[[Banff Springs Hotel]], [[Banff, Alberta|Banff]], [[Alberta]], Canada]]\nA [[destination hotel|destination resort]] is a resort that itself contains the necessary guest attraction capabilities so it does not need to be near a destination (town, historic site, theme park, or other) to attract its patrons. A commercial establishment at a resort destination such as a recreational area, a scenic or historic site, [[amusement park]], a gaming facility, or other tourist attraction may compete with other businesses at a destination. Consequently, another quality of a destination resort is that it offers food, drink, lodging, sports, entertainment, and shopping within the facility so that guests have no need to leave the facility throughout their stay.  Commonly, the facilities are of higher quality than would be expected if one were to stay at a hotel or eat in a town's restaurants. Some examples are Atlantis in the [[Bahamas]]; the [[Walt Disney World Resort]], near [[Orlando, Florida]], [[United States]]; [[PortAventura World]], near [[Barcelona]] on the [[Costa Daurada]] in [[Spain]]; Costa do Sau\u00edpe, [[Northeastern Brazil]]; Laguna Phuket, [[Thailand]] and Sun City, near [[Johannesburg]], [[South Africa]]. Closely related to resorts are convention and large meeting sites. Generally, they occur in cities, where special meeting halls, together with ample accommodations and varied dining and entertainment, are provided.\n\n== All-inclusive resort ==\n[[File:Happy Life Entrance.JPG|thumb|Entrance of an all-inclusive resort in [[Egypt]]]]\nAn all-inclusive resort charges a fixed price that includes most or all items.  At a minimum, most inclusive resorts include lodging, unlimited food, drink, sports activities, and entertainment for the fixed price. In recent years, the number of resorts in the United States offering \"all-inclusive\" amenities has decreased dramatically. In 1961, over half offered such plans, but in 2007, less than a tenth do so.<ref>{{cite news |first= |last= |authorlink= |coauthors= |title= American Plan resorts among last of vanishing breed |url= http://www.cnn.com/2007/TRAVEL/06/28/american.plan.ap/index.html|work=[[Associated Press]] |publisher=CNN.com |date=June 28, 2007 |accessdate= 2007-06-29 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20071012183847/http://cnn.com/2007/TRAVEL/06/28/american.plan.ap/index.html <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-10-12}}</ref>\n\nAll-inclusive resorts are found in the [[Caribbean]], particularly in [[Dominican Republic]]; in [[Egypt]], and elsewhere. Notable examples are [[Club Med]], [[Sandals Resorts]], and [[Beaches Resorts]].\n\nAn all-inclusive resort includes three meals daily, [[soft drink]]s, most [[alcoholic drink]]s, [[gratuities]], and usually other services in the price. Many also offer sports and other activities included in the price as well. They are often located in warmer regions. The all-inclusive model originated in the [[Club Med]] resorts, which were founded by the Belgian [[G\u00e9rard Blitz (entrepreneur)|G\u00e9rard Blitz]].<ref name=\"Garrett Nagle 1999\">{{cite book|title=Tourism, Leisure and Recreation|author=Garrett Nagle|year= 1999|publisher=Nelson Thornes|isbn=0-17-444705-1}}</ref>\n\nSome all-inclusive resorts are designed for specific groups. For example, some resorts cater for adults only, and even more-specialized properties accept couples only. Other all-inclusive resorts are geared toward families, with facilities like craft centers, game rooms, and water parks to keep children of all ages entertained. All-inclusive resorts are also very popular locations for destination weddings.\n[[File:Boating Resort in Vijayawada.jpg|250px|thumb|Boating resort in Vijayawada, India]]\n\n== Recreation ==\nA [[destination spa|spa resort]] is a short l-term residential/lodging facility with the primary purpose of providing individual services for spa goers to develop healthy habits. Historically, many such spas were developed at the location of natural hot springs or sources of mineral waters. Typically over a seven-day stay, such facilities provide a comprehensive program that includes spa services, physical fitness activities, healthy diet programs, and special interest programming.\n\nGolf resorts are resorts that cater specifically to the sport of [[golf]], and they include access to one or more golf courses and/or clubhouses. Golf resorts typically provide golf packages that provide visitors with all greens and cart fees, range balls, accommodations, and meals.\n\n[[File:Male Ciche.jpg|thumb|right|220px|A view of a typical ski resort and ski lifts]]\nIn [[North America]], a ski resort is generally a destination resort in a ski area. The term is less likely to refer to a town or village.\n\n[[File:Las Vegas 63.jpg|thumb|The [[Las Vegas strip]] in 2009]]\nA megaresort is a type of destination resort of an exceptionally-large size, such as those along the [[Las Vegas Strip]]. In [[Singapore]], ''[[integrated resort]]'' is a [[euphemism]] for a [[casino]]-based destination resort.\n\nA [[holiday village]] is a type of self-contained resort in [[Europe]] whose accommodation is generally in [[villa]]s.  A [[holiday camp]], in the [[United Kingdom]], refers to a resort whose accommodation is in [[chalet]]s or [[static caravan]]s.\n\n== Timeshare ==\nThere are more than 1500 [[timeshare]] resorts in the United States that are operated by major hospitality, timeshare-specific, or independent companies. They represent 198,000 residences and nearly 9 million owners, who pay an average $880 per year in maintenance fees. A reported 16% of the residences became [[vacation rentals]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nxtbook.com/ygsreprints/ARDA/g51820_arda_july2015/#/28|title=2015 State of the Industry |publisher=Developments|accessdate=July 1, 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Notable historic resorts ==\n* [[Baiae]], Italy, a famous historic resort of the ancient world that was popular over 2000 years ago. \n* [[Capri]], an island near [[Naples]], Italy, has attracted visitors since Roman times.\n* [[Monte Ne]], near [[Rogers, Arkansas]], a famous historic resort which was active in the early 20th century. At its peak, more than 10,000 people a year visited its hotels. Two of its hotels, Missouri Row and Oklahoma Row, were the largest log buildings in the world. Monte Ne closed in the 1930s and was ultimately submerged under [[Beaver Lake (Arkansas)|Beaver Lake]] in the 1960s.\n* Tawawa House, also known as Tawawa Springs or Xenia Springs, inspired [[Dolen Perkins-Valdez]] to write her [[debut novel]], ''Wench'' (2010),<ref>{{cite book|title=Wench|author=Perkins-Vadez, Dolen|publisher=Amistad|date=2010|asin=B004NE8RZ4}}</ref> when she read about it in an autobiography of [[W.E.B. Dubois]]. The book mentioned in passing that the land for [[Wilberforce University]] had once been used for a privately owned resort called Tawawa House, where white slave owners would bring the black slaves that they kept as mistresses.<ref>{{cite news|last1=O'Neal Parker|first1=Lonnae|title=A tender spot in master-slave relations|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2011/01/21/AR2011012102960.html|accessdate=15 April 2015|work=Washington Post}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hmdb.org/marker.asp?marker=14058|website=The Historical Marker Database|title= Old Wilberforce University Campus at Tawawa Springs |accessdate=May 28, 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Resort towns ==\nTowns that are resorts or in which [[tourism]] or vacationing is a major part of the local activity are sometimes called [[resort towns]]. If by the sea, they are called [[seaside resort]]s.  Inland resorts include [[ski resort]]s, [[mountain resort]]s and [[spa town]]s. Well-known resort towns include [[Punta Cana]] in [[Dominican Republic]], [[Bandipur]] in [[Nepal]], [[Bali]] in Indonesia, [[Sochi]] in [[Russia]], Mount Lebanon Tourism in [[Lebanon]], [[Barizo]] in [[Spain]], [[Cortina d'Ampezzo]] in Italy, [[Druskininkai]] in [[Lithuania]], [[Canc\u00fan]] in Mexico, [[Newport, Rhode Island]], and [[Key West, Florida]], in the United States, [[Ischgl]] in [[Austria]], [[St. Moritz]] in [[Switzerland]], [[Blackpool]] in the [[United Kingdom]] and [[Malam Jabba]] in [[Pakistan]].\n\n[[File:HuvafenFushi.jpg|thumb|A [[resort island]] in the [[Maldives]]]]\nA [[resort island]] is an island or an archipelago that contains resorts, hotels, restaurants, tourist attractions, and its amenities. [[Maldives]] is considered to have the best island resorts, which have become famous among the top celebrities and sportspersons around the world.\n\n[[File:Miamimetroarea.jpg|right|thumb|[[Miami Beach, Florida|Miami Beach]] in Florida]]\n[[Seaside resort]]s are located on a coast. In the United Kingdom, many seaside towns have turned to other entertainment industries, and some of them have much nightlife. The cinemas and theatres often remain to become host to a number of pubs, bars, restaurants, and nightclubs. Most of their entertainment facilities cater to local people, and the beaches still remain popular during the summer months.\n\nIn Europe and North America, [[ski resort]]s are towns and villages in ski areas, with support services for skiing such as hotels and [[chalet]]s, equipment rental, [[ski school]]s and [[ski lift]]s to access the slopes.\n\nResorts for different purposes also exist. An example is [[Yulara]], [[Northern Territory]], which exists to serve [[Uluru|Uluru (Ayers Rock)]] and [[Kata Tjuta|Kata Tjuta (The Olgas)]] in [[Australia]].\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Boutique hotel]]\n*[[Condo hotel]]\n*[[Destination club]]\n*[[Resort architecture]]\n*[[Sanatorium (resort)]]\n*[[Seaside resort]]\n*[[Spa]]\n*[[Vacation rental]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Commons category|Resorts}}\n{{Wiktionary}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{tourism}}\n\n[[Category:Resorts| ]]\n", "name_user": "190.186.20.23", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resort"}
{"title_page": "In Your Eyes (The Weeknd song)", "text_new": "{{short description|2020 single by The Weeknd}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name          = In Your Eyes\n| cover         =\n| type          = single\n| artist        = [[The Weeknd]]\n| album           = [[After Hours (The Weeknd album)|After Hours]]\n| released      = {{Start date|2020|03|24|mf=yes}}\n| format        = {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| recorded      =\n| studio        = \n* [[Conway Recording Studios|Conway]], [[Maratone Studios|MXM]] (Los Angeles, California)\n* House Mouse Studios, MXM (Stockholm, Sweden)\n| genre         = \n* [[Synth-pop]]<ref name=\"La Canci\u00f3n Del D\u00eda\"/>\n* [[post-disco]]<ref name=\"La Canci\u00f3n Del D\u00eda\"/>\n| length        = 3:57\n| label         = \n* [[XO (record label)|XO]]\n* [[Republic Records|Republic]]\n| writer        = \n* [[The Weeknd|Abel Tesfaye]]\n* [[Belly (rapper)|Ahmad Balshe]]\n* [[Max Martin]]\n* [[Oscar Holter]]\n| producer      = {{hlist|Max Martin|Oscar Holter|The Weeknd}}\n| chronology    = [[The Weeknd]]\n| prev_title    = [[Blinding Lights]]\n| prev_year     = 2019\n| next_title    = \n| next_year     = \n| misc          = {{External music video|{{YouTube|dqRZDebPIGs|In Your Eyes\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''In Your Eyes'''\" is a song by Canadian singer [[The Weeknd]] from his fourth studio album ''[[After Hours (The Weeknd album)|After Hours]]'' (2020).<ref>{{cite tweet|user=gthot20|number=1240851448952487936|title=@theweeknd \"In Your Eyes\" goes to pop radio next week...|date=March 20, 2020|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref> The song was serviced to [[contemporary hit radio]] on March 24, 2020 by [[XO (record label)|XO]] and [[Republic Records]] as the album's third single. It was originally released four days before, alongside the rest of its parent album.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rap-up.com/2020/03/17/the-weeknd-after-hours-tracklist/|title=The Weeknd Reveals 'After Hours' Tracklist|website=Rap-Up|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref> The Weeknd wrote and produced the song with [[Max Martin]] and [[Oscar Holter]], with Canadian rapper [[Belly (rapper)|Belly]] receiving additional writing credits as well.<ref name=\"Tidal\"/>\n\n==Background and release==\nThe song was first teased in The Weeknd's ''After Hours'' short film (released early March 2020) during a scene in which Tesfaye walked passed a musician playing the track's saxophone solo.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/the-weeknd-after-hours-short-film-watch-video-1203524075/|title=Watch The Weeknd\u2019s Disturbing Short Film for \u2018After Hours\u2019|first1=Jem|last1=Aswad|first2=Jem|last2=Aswad|date=March 4, 2020|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref> Later on, [[Island Records]] president Louis Bloom, in a mid-March 2020 interview with ''[[Music Week]]'' magazine, confirmed that a direct follow-up to \"[[Blinding Lights]]\" was set to be revealed upon the album's release.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-weeknds-label-boss-teases-big-follow-up-song-to-his-uk-number-1-blinding-lights-on-new-album-after-hours__29094/|title=The Weeknd's label boss teases big follow up to Blinding Lights|website=www.officialcharts.com|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref> The follow-up was then announced to be \"In Your Eyes\", with the song being added to various popular [[Spotify]] playlists and having its radio release confirmed by Gary Trust of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' magazine on March 20, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/playlist/37i9dQZF1DXcBWIGoYBM5M?si=yaY3bgEITAGYEhNhaEuWUg&_php=1|title=Today's Top Hits on Spotify (March 20, 2020)|date=March 20, 2020|website=Spotify|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320060128/https://open.spotify.com/playlist/37i9dQZF1DXcBWIGoYBM5M?si=yaY3bgEITAGYEhNhaEuWUg&_php=1|archive-date=March 20, 2020|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Lyrics==\nThe lyrics of the song reference Tesfaye's on-and-off relationship with model [[Bella Hadid]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/entertainment/news/twitter-thinks-the-weeknd-album-after-hours-is-about-bella-hadid/|title=Twitter Is Convinced The Weeknd\u2019s \u2018Entire\u2019 New Album Is About Bella Hadid|date=March 20, 2020|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hollywoodlife.com/2020/03/20/the-weeknd-after-hours-album-bella-hadid-songs/|title=The Weeknd\u2019s Fans Are Convinced That He Drops Multiple References To Bella Hadid In New Album|first=Jason Brow,Jade|last=Boren|date=March 20, 2020|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref> In the track, The Weeknd sings about feeling remorse over being unfaithful in the relationship that he had with his partner.<ref name=\"La Canci\u00f3n Del D\u00eda\"/> The song's lyrics serves as a contrast to the high energy and hopefulness found in the album's previous track \"[[Blinding Lights]]\", with the single taking on a more melancholic tone in its writing.<ref name=\"La Canci\u00f3n Del D\u00eda\"/>\n\n==Critical reception==\nThe song was noted as a standout track from the album by critics, with the single being compared to The Weeknd's previous radio hits.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/the-weeknd-looks-into-the-windows-of-the-soul-on-in-your-eyes-new-song.1986605.html|title=The Weeknd Looks Into The Windows Of The Soul On \"In Your Eyes\"|website=HotNewHipHop|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.breakingnews.fr/divertissement/the-weeknd-regarde-dans-les-fenetres-de-lame-sur-in-your-eyes-370470.html|title=The Weeknd regarde dans les fen\u00eatres de l'\u00e2me sur \"In Your Eyes\"|first=Breaking|last=News|date=March 20, 2020|website=Vivez l'actualit\u00e9 avec Breakingnews.fr|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref> Various journalists noted its heavy 80s influence, with the song's saxophone solo (performed by Wojtek Goral) and synths receiving praise and being compared to hits such as [[M83 (band)|M83]]'s \"[[Midnight City]]\" and [[Katy Perry]]'s \"[[Last Friday Night]]\".<ref name=\"La Canci\u00f3n Del D\u00eda\">{{Cite web|url=https://jenesaispop.com/2020/03/20/386848/la-cancion-del-dia-in-your-eyes-es-otra-gran-cancion-del-the-weeknd-mas-pop/|title=La Canci\u00f3n Del D\u00eda: 'In Your Eyes' es otra canci\u00f3n incontestable del The Weeknd m\u00e1s pop|date=March 20, 2020|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2020/03/20/7-albums-to-stream-weeknd-jbalvin-sada-baby|title=The 7 new albums you should stream right now|website=The FADER|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://djbooth.net/features/2020-03-20-the-weeknd-after-hours-album-review-new-music|title=The Weeknd \u2018After Hours\u2019 Album Review|first=Yoh|last=Phillips|website=DJBooth}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video for \"In Your Eyes\" was first teased by its director Anton Tammi on his [[Instagram]] story on March 21, 2020, with Tesfaye later on the following day posting the thumbnail for the visual on his social media accounts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/screenshot20200321220414|title=Screenshots of Anton Tammi's Instagram Story on March 21, 2020|publisher=Instagram|accessdate=March 23, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|user=TheWeeknd|number=1241768186359328769|title=saga continues tomorrow - The Weeknd|date=March 22, 2020|accessdate=March 23, 2020}}</ref> Its confirmation as the music video for the single was confirmed eleven hours before its release, with the video premiering on March 23, 2020.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=TheWeeknd|number=1241950188060606464|title=tune in, in the morning - The Weeknd|date=March 23, 2020|accessdate=March 23, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2020/03/23/the-weeknd-in-your-eyes-video|title=The Weeknd shares \"In Your Eyes\" video|website=The Fader|accessdate=March 23, 2020}}</ref> The visual stars Zaina Miuccia as the lead female protagonist and continues the storyline from the ''[[After Hours (The Weeknd album)#Release and promotion|After Hours]]'' short film after The Weeknd enters the elevator with the couple.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/the-weeknd-loses-his-head-in-gory-new-in-your-eyes-video/|title=The Weeknd Loses His Head in Gory New \"In Your Eyes\" Video|website=Pitchfork|accessdate=March 23, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-C3mwpprka/|title=Anton Tammi on Instagram: \"saga continues tomorrow. starring: Zaina Miuccia @theweeknd\"|website=Instagram|accessdate=March 23, 2020}}</ref> In the music video, The Weeknd, after having killed Miuccia's companion in the aforementioned elevator, chases her throughout different locations until they reach a nightclub named After Hours. There, Miuccia manages to grab an axe that she then uses to decapitate the Weeknd, with her then proceeding to dance with his lifeless head throughout the rest of the music video.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2020/03/the-weeknd-in-your-eyes-video|title=The Weeknd Shares Blood-Soaked \"In Your Eyes\" Video|website=Complex|accessdate=March 23, 2020}}</ref> The visual features the return of Wojtek Goral as the saxophone player from the album's self-titled short film and was compared to the slasher movies of the 1980s, being met with a positive reception.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stereogum.com/2077699/the-weeknds-in-your-eyes-video-is-an-amazing-slasher-movie-parody/video/|title=The Weeknd's \"In Your Eyes\" Video Is An Amazing Slasher-Movie Parody: Watch|date=March 23, 2020|accessdate=March 23, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\nFollowing the releasing of its parent album, \"In Your Eyes\" debuted at number 16 on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] dated April 4, 2020. It was the highest overall debut of the week and third highest charting track from ''After Hours''.<ref name=\"Hot 100 Peak\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/amp/articles/business/chart-beat/9346588/every-song-weeknd-after-hours-hot-100|title=Every Song From The Weeknd's 'After Hours' Is on the Hot 100|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Zellener|first=Xander|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe song debuted at number 17 on the [[UK Singles Chart]], becoming his 20th top 40 hit on the chart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/22895/weeknd/|title=The Weeknd {{!}} full Official Chart History {{!}} Official Charts Company|website=www.officialcharts.com|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> Elsewhere in Europe, it managed to debut in the top 20 of the Belgian Tip charts, Irish Singles Chart, and Dutch Single Top 100. The song also managed to debut within the top ten of Norwegian and Swedish charts, with the single also reaching a top 40 position of number 26 in Italy.<!-- See charts section. -->\n\n==Personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref name=\"Tidal\">{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/134815153|title=After Hours / The Weeknd \u2013 Tidal|website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref> \n* [[The Weeknd]] \u2013 vocals, songwriting, production\n* [[Belly (rapper)|Belly]] \u2013 songwriting\n* [[Max Martin]] \u2013 songwriting, production\n* [[Oscar Holter]] \u2013 songwriting, production\n* Dave Kutch \u2013 mastering \n* Kevin Peterson \u2013 mastering\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Australia|13|artist=The Weeknd|song=In Your Eyes|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|23|artist=The Weeknd|rowheader=true|song=In Your Eyes|accessdate=April 2, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|30|artist=The Weeknd|song=In Your Eyes|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia Tip|1|artist=The Weeknd|song=In Your Eyes|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 