om/polls/20200309_MI.pdf AtlasIntel]\n|Mar 7\u20139, 2020\n|1,100 (RV)\n|\u00b1 3.0 %\n|{{party shading/Republican}}|'''46%'''\n|44%\n| 10%\n| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [https://www.monmouth.edu/polling-institute/reports/monmouthpoll_MI_030920/ Monmouth University]\n|Mar 5\u20138, 2020\n|977 (RV)\n|\u00b1 3.1 %\n|41%\n|{{party shading/Democratic}}|'''48%'''\n| 2%\n| 9%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [https://firehousestrategies.com/analysis/december_2019_battleground_survey/ Firehouse Strategies/\u00d8ptimus]\n|Mar 5\u20137, 2020\n|550 (RV)\n|\u00b1 5.3 %\n|{{party shading/Republican}}|'''46%'''\n|44%\n| \u2013\n| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [https://news.wisc.edu/battleground-state-poll-1/ YouGov]\n|Feb 11\u201320, 2020\n|1,249 (RV)\n|\u00b1 4.0 %\n|43%\n|{{party shading/Democratic}}|'''47%'''\n| \u2013\n| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [https://poll.qu.edu/2020-presidential-swing-state-polls/release-detail?ReleaseID=3656 Quinnipiac University]\n|Feb 12\u201318, 2020\n|845 (RV)\n|\u00b1 3.4 %\n|43%\n|{{party shading/Democratic}}|'''47%'''\n|6%{{efn|\"Someone else\" with 2%; would not vote with 4%}}\n|3%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[https://www.progressivepolicy.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/PPI_SwingVoterPoll_Feb2020.pdf Expedition Strategies/Progressive Policies Institute]\n| Feb 6-18, 2020\n| 500 (RV)\n| \u2013\n| '''43%''' \n| '''43%'''\n| \u2013\n| 14%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[https://ssl2002.webhosting.comcast.net/epic-mra/press/Stwd_Survey_Jan2020_Media_Freq.pdf EPIC-MRA/Detroit Free Press][https://eu.freep.com/story/news/politics/elections/2020/01/15/mike-bloomberg-other-democrats-lead-donald-trump-michigan-poll/4469175002/]\n| Jan 9\u201312, 2020\n| 600 (LV)\n| \u00b1 4%\n| 44%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}}|'''50%'''\n| \u2013\n| 6%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [https://www.scribd.com/document/442183414/January-2020-Statewide-Survey Glengariff Group Inc.]\n| Jan 3\u20137, 2020\n| 600 (LV)